Cura ut praestes] i. esec ut milri caveas ab r‘stis Pompeii asseclis, ne eos competitores habeam, Schiitz. But ‘take care to secure me the votes of his retinue' is certainly the more natural interpretation of the words, and more in accordance with the ordinary usage of praestare.

Illam manum] i. e. the influential voters who had accom- panied Pompeius on his Mithridatia campaign. The phrase praestare illam manum may refer to their votes or else to their indirect influence. It is not necessary to confine it to the latter, as from the sentence which follows it seems clear that some of them, if not Pompeius himself, would be able to attend in person at the election.
